144 void ArmUsInfoSimul::calculate_motor_velocities()
145 {
146  // Joint mode
147  if (MoveMode == MovementMode::Joint)
148  {
149  MotorVelocities.set(JointCommand, JointControlled);
150  }
151 
152  // Cartesian mode
153  else if (MoveMode == MovementMode::Cartesian)
154  {
155  Vector3f velocities = { 0.f, 0.f, 0.f }; // Joint velocities returned from the service
156  int singularMatrix = 0; // Int that expresses if the service encountered a singular matrix
157 
158  // Call the function in Arm Us that calls the serive
159  // Returns true if the service call was successful, false otherwise
160  bool service_success = static_cast<bool>(mf_call_inv_kin_calc_service(velocities, singularMatrix));
161 
162  if (service_success == false)
163  {
164  // ROS_ERROR("Inverse kinematic calculation service not called");
165  }
166  else
167  {
168  MotorVelocities.m1 = velocities.x;
169  MotorVelocities.m2 = velocities.y;
170  MotorVelocities.m3 = velocities.z;
171  }
172  }
173 }

187 void ArmUsInfoReal::calculate_motor_velocities()
188 {
189  // Joint mode
190  if (MoveMode == MovementMode::Joint)
191  {
192  // Joints 1 and 2 are controlled by a differential
193  // A combination of the first two motors is needed to make the proper rotations
194 
195  // Both motors make the two big gears rotate in the same direction, making the arm go up or down
196  // Negative sign is needed on motor 2 since motors are facing opposite directions in assembly
197  if (JointControlled == 1)
198  {
199  MotorVelocities.m1 = JointCommand;
200  MotorVelocities.m2 = -JointCommand;
201  }
202 
203  // Both motors make the two big gears rotate in te opposite direction, making the arm go left or right
204  // Negative sign is NOT needed on motor 2 since motors are facing opposite directions in assembly
205  else if (JointControlled == 2)
206  {
207  MotorVelocities.m1 = JointCommand;
208  MotorVelocities.m2 = JointCommand;
209  }
210 
211  // Other joints are controlled by one motor each
212  else
213  {
214  MotorVelocities.set(JointCommand, JointControlled);
215  }
216  }
217 
218  // Cartesian mode
219  else if (MoveMode == MovementMode::Cartesian)
220  {
221  Vector3f velocities = { 0.f, 0.f, 0.f }; // Joint velocities returned from the service
222  int singularMatrix = 0; // Int that expresses if the service encountered a singular matrix
223 
224  // Call the function in Arm Us that calls the serive
225  // Returns true if the service call was successful, false otherwise
226  bool service_success = static_cast<bool>(mf_call_inv_kin_calc_service(velocities, singularMatrix));
227 
228  if (service_success == false)
229  {
230  // ROS_ERROR("Inverse kinematic calculation service not called");
231  }
232  else
233  {
234  MotorVelocities.m1 = (velocities.x + velocities.y) / 2;
235  MotorVelocities.m2 = (-velocities.x + velocities.y) / 2;
236  MotorVelocities.m3 = velocities.z;
237  }
238  }
239 };
